<div class="pals-info clear">
<h3>PALS (Patient advice and liaison service)</h3>
<p><a href="mailto:pals.qeht@nhs.net">pals.qeht@nhs.net</a></p>
<div class="pals-text">
<p>You can talk to PALS who provide confidential advice and support to patients, families and their carers, and can provide information on the NHS and health related matters.</p>
<p>The Patient Advice and Liaison Service (PALS) provide patients, their families and carers with information, advice and support about NHS services.<br/>Sometimes people do not know where to turn to get help. PALS can be the first port of call.<br/><br/>The PALS team aims to:<br/><br/>Sort out problems quickly on your behalf<br/>Listen to your concerns, suggestions and queries<br/>Provide a voice to give real weight to your experience<br/>Supply information on NHS services<br/>We have a dedicated PALS office at Queen Elizabeth, Woolwich. Alternatively, arrangements can be made for a member of the PALS team to visit the patient on the ward. These visits can be arranged through the Ward Manager or a member of staff.<br/><br/>How to make a complaint<br/>If we cannot resolve your concern to your satisfaction, we will advise you how to take the matter forward using the formal complaints procedure.</p>
</div>
<div class="box">
<h4>PALS</h4>
<dl class="pals clear">
<dt>Tel:</dt>
<dd>020 8836 4592
